FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - UK (ENGLAND) (29)
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: Tue 18 Sep 2007
Source: DEFRA Information Bulletin, ref 303/07 [edited]
<http://www.defra.gov.uk/news/2007/070918a.htm>

FMD update: further tests confirm FMD at slaughter on suspicion site in Surrey
--------------------------------------------------
Foot and mouth disease (FMD) has today [18 Sep 2007] been confirmed at the
slaughter on suspicion premises where sheep, pigs, and cattle were culled
last night [17 Sep 2007]. This now becomes the 5th Infected Premises since
3 Aug 2007.
When the animals were examined at slaughter they showed FMD lesions.
Results of further laboratory tests are awaited.
The farm is within the existing Protection Zone near to the Infected
Premises confirmed last week [10-16 Sep 2007].
Minor changes have now been made to the Protection Zones (PZ) and
Surveillance Zone (SZ) in the area.
The new zones, [including map], can be found at
<http://www.defra.gov.uk/footandmouth/pdf/declaration-amdning-pzsz180907.pdf>
--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Mary Marshall
